				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\times$$\end{document}8) logic array consisting of 64 SPPD pixels successfully executed the five basic logic gates at 100% accuracy, insusceptible to electrical noise or current variation between the pixels owing to bipolar photoresponse.

To theoretically evidence the bipolar spectral photoresponse, we performed an optical field simulation. A charge generation rate (CR), occurring along a coronal plane of the back-to-back structure, was simulated under monochromatic irradiation (400–1000 nm). The CR was calculated as follows:1CR=2πε0nkh∥E∥2,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
